ol.li:
approximate preservation of
        the presence (and therefore timing) of congestion marks on the L2
        frames used to construct an IP packet;

li.t:
at high frequency of congestion
            marking, approximate preservation of the proportion of congestion
            marks arriving and departing;

ul.li:
A wide range of tunnelling protocols, including those with various
          forms of shim header between two IP headers, possibly also separated
          by an L2 header;
